      "author": "mattmcmanus",
      "description": "## New\n\n- **Target folder for standalone moments** (#14) — choose where standalone moment notes are created. A new **Default folder** setting (under **Settings → Moments → Standalone notes**) sets the default, and the **Create new moment note** modal now has a **Folder** field, pre-filled and editable per-creation, with folder autocomplete. A missing folder is created automatically. Leaving it blank falls back to Obsidian's new-note location, so existing behavior is unchanged.\n\n## Fixes\n\n- Timeline title ellipsis and auto-loading pagination\n- Moved the modal **Create** button to the right\n- Evaluate template placeholders when creating standalone notes\n\n## Install\n\nCopy `main.js`, `manifest.json`, and `styles.css` into `<Vault>/.obsidian/plugins/moments/`.",
